SIMPLE: eighth
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eighth
<hw>Eighth</hw> <pr>(⟦amac⟧tth)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>eahto⟦edh⟧a</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Next in order after the
seventh.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Consisting of one of eight equal divisions of a
thing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Eighth note</b></col> <fld>(Mus.)</fld>, <cd>the eighth
part of a whole note, or semibreve; a quaver.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eighth</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Eighth
<hw>Eighth</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quotient of a unit
divided by eight; one of eight equal parts; an eighth part.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>The interval of an
octave.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eighthly</ent>⟦br⟧
